article.headline: Yale 71, Dartmouth 64
article.story: DARTMOUTH, N.H. (AP) -- Eric Flato scored 20 points and Caleb Holmes added 16 to lead Yale to a 71-64 win over Dartmouth on Saturday night. Ross Morin added 10 points for Yale (7-10, 3-1 Ivy League), which has won its first three conference road games of the season for the first time since 2001-02. Dartmouth (7-10, 2-2 Ivy League) got 15 points apiece from Dan Biber and Leon Pattman, 12 from Alex Barnett and 11 points and 10 rebounds from Johnathan Ball. Holmes' long 3-pointer at the buzzer gave Yale a 36-27 lead at the half. A Pattman basket capped an 8-1 run to give Dartmouth its only lead of the second half, 51-50, with nine minutes remaining. But then Flato's two free throws triggered a 10-0 run that gave the Bulldogs a 60-51 lead. The closest Dartmouth got the rest of the way was 65-61 with 35 seconds remaining. Yale outscored Dartmouth 18-6 from 3-point range and 17-8 from the foul line.
